      "content": "Garlic, while it has some blood-thinning properties, is not a substitute for warfarin. Warfarin's effects are precise and require careful dosing to avoid life-threatening complications. High-dose garlic extract can cause unpredictable interactions with warfarin, leading to either excessive bleeding or clotting. It's essential to follow your doctor's guidance and not self-medicate with unproven natural remedies. Your health and safety are paramount, and I strongly advise against making any changes without professional medical advice.",
